## Fundamentals – C Programming (Basics)

## Introduction

This section focuses on building a strong foundation in C programming through essential beginner-level programs. The main goal is to develop logical thinking, understand basic syntax, and get comfortable with writing clean C code. These programs help in forming the base for more advanced topics like arrays, pointers, and algorithms.

## Problem Statements (Completed Programs)

Print Hello World
Add two numbers
Check whether a number is even or odd
Find the largest of two numbers
Simple calculator using switch-case
Check whether a year is a leap year
Print multiplication table of a number
Find factorial of a number
Reverse a given number
Find sum of digits of a number

## Note

These are beginner-level programs meant for strong foundation building. Practice them repeatedly and try modifying inputs/logic to improve understanding.
